            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I wonder if we should prefix these with `nvim.` ? \n\nOr alternatively, maybe we should error if a plugin tries to set `id` to a non-prefixed string. So Nvim owns the non-prefixed namespace. OTOH, that may be confusing given that Nvim owns the `nvim.*` namespace for augroups, namespaces, etc.",
